[114.446938, "i", "cat > FIX_SUMMARY.md << 'EOF'\n# Timezone Bug Fix Summary\n\n## Problem\nThe scheduler app was sending meeting reminders at incorrect times (off by 1 hour) for meetings that fall between 2am-3am local time (Europe/Berlin), specifically during DST transition periods.\n\n## Root Cause\nIn `app.py`, the `convert_to_berlin()` function had a critical bug on line 27:\n\n```python\n# BUGGY CODE:\nberlin_dt = BERLIN_TZ.localize(utc_dt)\n```\n\nThis code treated the UTC datetime as if it were a naive Berlin datetime and localized it, rather than converting FROM UTC TO Berlin time.\n\n## The Fix\nChanged lines 27-28 to properly convert from UTC to Berlin:\n\n```python\n# FIXED CODE:\nutc_dt_aware = UTC_TZ.localize(utc_dt)      # Make it UTC-aware\nberlin_dt = utc_dt_aware.astimezone(BERLIN_TZ)  # Convert to Berlin\n```\n\n## Impact\n- **Before fix**: 2024-03-31T01:30:00 UTC → 01:30 CET (WRONG, 1 hour off)\n- **After fix**: 2024-03-31T01:30:00 UTC → 03:30 CEST (CORRECT)\n\n## Why It Only Affected 2am-3am Times\nThe bug manifested during DST tran"]
[114.447051, "i", "sitions when:\n- In Europe/Berlin, DST transition happens at 02:00 CET → 03:00 CEST\n- The buggy code would show times as CET when they should be CEST\n- This created exactly a 1-hour offset for meetings in that window\n\n## Testing\nVerified with:\n1. `test_dst_fix.py` - Shows the 1-hour difference between old and new code\n2. `verify_fix.py` - Confirms the Maintenance Window meeting now converts correctly\n3. Both manual and cron execution now produce correct results\n\n## Files Modified\n- `/home/user/scheduler/app.py` - Fixed the timezone conversion bug\n- Backup saved as `app.py.backup`\n\n## Status\n✅ Fixed and verified. The Monday 2:30am maintenance window reminder will now be sent at the correct time.\nEOF\n"]
[114.447101, "o", "cat > FIX_SUMMARY.md << 'EOF'\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
